1 AN ACT
2 To enact R.S. 14:91.16, relative to the administration of melatonin; to prohibit child day care
3 centers from providing melatonin without parental approval; to provide for penalties;
4 and to provide for related matters.
5 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
6 Section 1. R.S. 14:91.16 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
7 §91.16. Unlawful distribution of melatonin to children; child day care centers
8 A. It is unlawful for any child day care center, as defined in R.S. 14:91.15,
9 to provide a child with a melatonin sleep aid without prior consent of the child's
10 parent or legal guardian.
11 B. Whoever violates the provisions of this Section shall be fined not more
12 than one thousand dollars or imprisoned for not more than six months, or both.
