HB 106 Original 2026 Regular Session Cox
Abstract: Prohibits day care facilities from providing a child with melatonin without
parental approval.
Proposed law prohibits a child day care facility from providing a child with melatonin unless
the child's parent or legal guardian has previously consented.
Proposed law provides a penalty of a fine up to $1,000 or up to 6 months in jail, or both.
(Adds R.S. 14:91.16)
